MET00J: Validate method arguments
Description:
Method arguments should be validated to make sure that they align with the methodâ€™s intended design and structure. Invalid arguments can lead to runtime exceptions, incorrect calculations, and other issues. When defensive programming is required, do so for just one side of the caller/callee relationship. 
Why is it important:
This is important because an attacker could pass invalid arguments to a method that contains sensitive or important structural data. They may find vulnerabilities in the system from doing so.
